{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"alias":"cursorial-unallergic-allosaurus","description":"## Why\n\nEnforcement is the goal of the epic, but it must land **only after** every writer signs\n(stories: local, GitHub Actions, Gerrit) and grandfathering is proven (grandfathering story).\nFlipping early turns every push red by construction (bug 27ae). This story is the final,\natomic switch.\n\n## What\n\nEnable enforcement in a single change:\n\n- In `rebar.toml`, set `[identity] require_authenticated = true` alongside the pinned\n  `enforce_since`, in **one** change.\n- Confirm the merge-gate now enforces (fails on a new in-scope unsigned/forged event) while\n  all three writer surfaces continue to pass.\n\n## Scope\n\nThe one-line config flip + verification. Depends on the local, GitHub Actions, Gerrit, and\ngrandfathering stories all being complete and confirmed.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `identity.require_authenticated = true` and the pinned `enforce_since` land in **one**\n      change.\n- [ ] After the flip, `rebar verify-identity` FAILS on a new in-scope unsigned/forged event\n      (non-zero exit). Proving command: introduce a synthetic unsigned in-scope event and\n      confirm the gate rejects it.\n- [ ] All three writer surfaces (local, CI, Gerrit) continue to pass the enforcing gate — no\n      red pushes on `main`.","id":"8d39-85d7-8f34-45e6","parent_id":"dc09-6565-cf85-4aea","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"Flip identity.require_authenticated=true with pinned enforce_since in one change"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1784226857982563001,"uuid":"81d37a0d-bb84-4c69-b4c4-e4e570d17bd5"}